column4: Hey, I need help with my dell inspiron 6400 laptop, the wireless isn't working and I've done all the stuff that it says in this faq: http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=297092&highlight=dell+1390+ndiswrapper
I'm at a complete loss
My wireless simply won't connect
have you turned the hardware switch for wireless 'On'?
I'll check
I don't think there is a physical switch
Do you know any reasons why or why not my wireless isn't workinig?
The wifi light isn't on but the bluetooth light is on
I wish you cared about a simple man with no wireless
Do you hate me?
have you installed the driver?
Dell Inspiron 6400
I have done everything in this faq: http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=297092&highlight=dell+1390+ndiswrapper
Standard ndiswrapper crap
why have you bought a computer with a wireless card that is manufactured by someone not caring about Linux support?
It's not mine, I stole it from a black person who isn't very well off.
Just kidding
No
It's my girlfriends
She has no idea about GNU ideology nor does she care. I'm putting linux on here to kind of introduce her to using different (and better) operating systems.
I never have had the need to mess around with ndis wrapper so I'm not able to help, sorry
Thanks anyway
